01/09/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The government has vowed to intensify efforts to combat human trafficking, Deputy Foreign Minister Andreas Loverdos said on Friday (29 August).
He added that the government plans to grant 1.1m euros in 2004 to support NGO activities aimed at protecting victims of trafficking.
The cabinet also plans to establish a team to monitor and co-ordinate NGO efforts targeting the problem.
(ANA, MPA - 29/08/03)
